**Implementing Type Casts**

I've been working on a new approach to resolve the type-related errors. By explicitly casting `FileList` to `File[]` and making corresponding changes in the `map` and `filter` functions, I expect to eliminate all the issues with the object spread, and ensure that the `File` type has the `text()` method, eliminating issues at line 325. This should provide the necessary clarity for the compiler. I've updated the XML file accordingly.


**Implementing Promises and Typing**

I'm now revisiting the `text()` method, realizing it returns a Promise. I need to handle these promises correctly when mapping `textFiles`. Also, in `StatisticsDisplay.tsx`, I will try to explicitly include `id` in the returned object, and also be sure I've imported `PlaybackStat` correctly. I will also be sure to type all variables and functions correctly, in both files.

```typescript
// App.tsx
import React, { useState, useCallback, useEffect } from 'react';
import type { PlaybackStat, PlaybackStats } from './services/localStorageService';
import { readAndWriteFiles, loadAllFiles, loadOneFile } from './services/fileService';

function App() {
  const [fileList, setFileList] = useState<FileList | null>(null);
  const [textFiles, setTextFiles] = useState<File[]>([]);
  const [stats, setStats] = useState<PlaybackStats>({});

  const loadFiles = useCallback(() => {
    if (fileList === null) return;
    const filesArray = Array.from(fileList);
    setTextFiles(filesArray);

    const allContentPromises = filesArray.map(file => file.text());

    Promise.all(allContentPromises)
      .then(contents => {
        readAndWriteFiles(contents, filesArray, setStats);
      })
      .catch(error => console.error('Error reading files:', error));
  }, [fileList]);

  useEffect(() => {
    loadAllFiles(setStats);
  }, []);

  const handleFileChange = (e: React.ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>) => {
    setFileList(e.target.files);
  };

  useEffect(() => {
    loadFiles();
  }, [fileList, loadFiles]);

  return (
    <div>
      <input type="file" multiple onChange={handleFileChange} />
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;
```

```typescript
// components/StatisticsDisplay.tsx
import React, { useMemo } from 'react';
import type { PlaybackStats, PlaybackStat } from '../services/localStorageService';

const StatRow: React.FC<{ stat: PlaybackStat & { id: string } }> = ({ stat }) => (
    <div>
        <div>ID: {stat.id}</div>
        <div>Last Played: {new Date(stat.lastPlayed).toLocaleString()}</div>
    </div>
);

const StatisticsDisplay: React.FC<{ stats: PlaybackStats }> = ({ stats }) => {
    const sortedStats = useMemo(() => {
        return Object.entries(stats)
            .map(([id, data]) => ({ id, ...data as PlaybackStat }))
            .sort((a, b) => new Date(b.lastPlayed).getTime() - new Date(a.lastPlayed).getTime());
    }, [stats]);

    return (
        <div>
            {sortedStats.map(stat => (
                <StatRow key={stat.id} stat={stat} />
            ))}
        </div>
    );
};

export default StatisticsDisplay;
```


